  }, "1")), " Miners can \"pool\" their computational energy together to increase the chances of finding a proof-of-work and adding a new block. In fact if the original purpose of bitcoin was to give every user a chance of using their own computers to \"passively\" generate income through mining (and eventually validating), the computational and energy needs are so immense that roughly 65-70% of the world's mining activity occurs in data centers in China.", mdx("sup", {
