    "className": "footnote-ref"
  }, "3"))), mdx("p", null, "To go one level up, decentralized autonomous organizations (DAOs) claim to provide a democratic way for currency owners to participate in governance of Ethereum and the way rewards are spent. However, the accretion of membership within mining pools and DAOs can give these groups more political power to deterimine the course of ethereum than individual users, thus setting up differing classes of citizenship in the community."), mdx("h2", null, "Carbon Offsetting Is Flawed"), mdx("p", null, "Given the state of the world in the past two decades, the more activistic of Gen-Z and millennial consumers are pressuring companies to take social responsibility into account, raising issues of environmental racism, human rights and in employment and manufacturing practices. And companies have in turn responded with promises to pay reasonable wages, provide work life balance, foozeball tables, etc."), mdx("p", null, "We want our art and passion work to be morally hygienic, the meat we eat to have happily died for us. The cognitive dissonance has never been stronger and carbon offsetting begs the question of whether the ends justifies the means. (Not to make light of our general gig-working artist who has 2 or 3 precarious jobs, most of which have been made redundant by Covid.)"), mdx("p", null, "There's a ton already written out there on this subject so I won't belabor it.", mdx("sup", {
